Package: neosnatch
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Not your Daddy's Neofetch
 neosnatch displays operator-relevant system status on interactive shell
 login: load average, memory and disk pressure, listening services and
 their owning processes, Docker network names, failed systemd units,
 pending security advisories, public IP, active sessions, and last login.
 .
 A privileged snapshot collector runs every 5 minutes via systemd timer
 to capture data that requires root (process names of foreign sockets,
 docker network IDs, failed unit list); the unprivileged login binary
 reads the snapshot and merges it into live facts without elevating.
